Package datareadwrite

Class AppointmentReader

Object
AppointmentReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
DataReader
public class AppointmentReader extends Object implements DataReader
The AppointmentReader class implements the DataReader interface to read and load Appointment data from a CSV file into the system's data storage.

This class is responsible for parsing the contents of a CSV file containing Appointment attributes, such as the patientid, date, and time etc. It then creates Appointment objects and adds them to the system's inventory.

It reads the data from the Medicine_List.csv file, which is expected to have the following format: 

 Appointment ID Patient ID      Doctor ID       Appointment Status      Appointment Date        Appointment Time        Appointment Type        Prescribed Medications  Consultation Notes

The populateData method processes each line in the CSV, creates a Appointment object for each entry, and stores it in the DataStorage object's inventory.
